" Learning advices
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
A Summary from [ https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ke7SfUFvvxo ]

1. Learn to use vim help
  - Spend a few minitues a day in vim help.

2. Keep a cheetsheet
  - 7 to 10 commands on your cheetsheet. 
  - Be aware of these commands' existence and opportunities you can use them.

3. Keep track of your common mistakes

4. Learn all single letter commands
   [ http://hea-www.harvard.edu/~fine/Tech/vi.html ]

"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
" My vim cheetsheet 
"""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""""
1. Shift N to search in the "opposite" direction.
2. \w to open a url link on browser from vim. [due to my vimrc config]

